Planning UI: declare and remove player signals

The footer SIGNALS line is now a button that opens a manager picker:
remove any declared signal, or add one from the preset palette
(advance/charge/retreat/hold/flank/regroup/rally/fire), capped at 4.
SignalsText is always actionable, even when none are declared.

Adds PlanDraft.RemovePlayerSignal (case-insensitive) with a test
covering declare/dedup/cap-at-4/remove. 250 Core tests pass.

Verified in-game: adding 'retreat' updates the SIGNALS line to
[advance] [charge] [retreat] and reports the change in the status line.
